modules.description: This module provides functions to create, modify, and extract zip files. It operates on file paths and directories, allowing recursive compression, selective extraction, and direct file manipulation within zip archives. Concrete use cases include packaging application assets, updating specific files in an archive, and extracting dependencies during deployment.

This module handles zip file operations including creation, modification, and extraction. It works with file paths and directories to support recursive compression, selective extraction, and in-archive file updates. Use cases include bundling application resources, modifying specific archive contents, and deploying dependencies via extraction.
